The paper deals with the problem of selecting representatives from a data set for learning tasks, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The paper proposes a new algorithm for exemplar selection, which involves convex optimization and dictionary learning. These topics are closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). Given the focus on machine learning and data analysis, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.IT.
